==Hindi==
===Demonstrative pronoun===
'''उन''' (un)

# [[those]] - [[oblique]] case only, see below for direct. (Singular: [[उस]])
#:Example: "उन मकानों [[में]] [[छह]] कमरे हैं" - "In thदse houses there are six rooms." Literally - "These houses in six rooms are."
# [[him]] - oblique case only, far reference, polite. (If no additional [[respect]] is conveyed, [[उस]] is used)
#:Example: "उनको [[पैसे]] [[देना|दे]] [[दो]]" - Give money to him. Literally "Him to money give."
# [[her]] - oblique case only, far reference. (If no additional [[respect]] is conveyed, उस is used)
#:Example "उनको पैसे दे दो" - Give money to her. (The same)
# [[it]] - oblique case only.
#:Example "उन [[लेना|लो]]" - Take those.

====Inflection====
[[Direct]]: [[वे]]
Direct, singular, far reference: [[वह]](vah) - [[That]]

===See also===
*[[इन]](in) - [[These]], [[him]] and [[her]] (near reference).

